"'''A Barve Like That: The Tale of Boba Fett'''" by [[Daniel Keys Moran|J.D. Montgomery]] appeared in ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'', which was published [[December]] [[1995]] by [[Bantam Spectra]]. It tells the story of how [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] escaped the [[Sarlacc/Legends|sarlacc]].

==Plot summary==
[[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] awakens inside the [[Sarlacc/Legends|Sarlacc]]. Via the Sarlacc, he makes [[Telepathy/Legends|telepathic]] contact with the first of its victims, [[Susejo]]. A series of flashbacks ensues, showing some of the sarlacc's other victims, including a pair of [[Corellian/Legends|Corellians]] and a [[Unidentified female Jedi (sarlacc)|Jedi]]. Other flashbacks detail Boba Fett's delivery of the frozen [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] to [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]].

Inside the Sarlacc, for some time Fett is immobilized and his [[Mandalorian armor/Legends|armor]] is heavily damaged by the creature's digestive system. He learns that Susejo can exert some control over the Sarlacc. He goads Susejo, making the beast contract around his [[Jetpack/Legends|jetpack]]. The resulting explosion frees the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] from the Sarlacc's grasp. He then fires [[Concussion grenade/Legends|concussion grenades]] into the wall of the beast, blowing a hole in its interior. Boba Fett escapes the Sarlacc, which like him is badly injured but still alive.

[[5 ABY/Legends|A year later]], Fett returns to the Sarlacc in the ''[[Slave II]]''. Due to his prior contact with the it, he can reestablish the telepathic connection with Susejo. He decides not to destroy the Sarlacc yet, but promises to return.

==Continuity==
Artwork accompanying this story in ''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' depicts [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] as having lost his left leg within the [[Sarlacc/Legends|Sarlacc]].<ref name="TERC" /> This was not mentioned in this story; however, post&ndash;[[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]] sections of "[[The Last One Standing: The Tale of Boba Fett]]" describe him using a [[Cybernetics|prosthesis]] on his right leg, below his knee, not his left leg. ''[[The Bounty Hunter Wars]]'' and later [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] works do not reference this.

Fett's battle with [[IG-88C/Legends|IG-88]] was later portrayed in the comic book ''[[Battle of the Bounty Hunters]]'' and [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (comic series)|''Shadows of the Empire'' comic]]. Another version, where Fett destroys [[IG-88B/Legends|IG-88B]] on [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]], then C and [[IG-88D/Legends|D]] in a dogfight over [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], was depicted in "[[Therefore I Am: The Tale of IG-88]]."

Taking into account all stories, this was the second time Fett has escaped the [[Sarlacc/Legends|Sarlacc]]. The [[Star Wars (1977)|Marvel Comics]] story "Jawas of Doom!" in [[Star Wars (1977) 81|''Star Wars'' #81]] ([[1984]]) has Fett regurgitated by a dyspeptic Sarlacc. Despite a temporary bout of amnesia, he is relatively intact – armor and all. By tale's end, though, he once again fell into the same Sarlacc. This second round was much more debilitating, as this short story described the burns and broken bones Fett sustained within the beast's gullet. The story of ''[[The Bounty Hunter Wars]]'' ([[1998]]-[[1999]]) occurs in the year long gap found in this short story's finale.<ref name="TERC" />

J.D. Montgomery is actually a pseudonym that was used for this story by the author [[Daniel Keys Moran]].<ref name="TERC" />

